The paper deals with image segmentation, specifically for fingerprint images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of different segmentation algorithms, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of filters and signal processing techniques is also mentioned, which could fall under computer networks and communications (cs.CR). Finally, the paper compares different algorithms and proposes a new method, which could be considered machine learning (cs.LG).
